#: src/pages/docs/CastingHelpPage.tsx:57
msgid "Cast playback is Tier D on the sync ladder: seconds-class glass-to-glass latency, typically 6–30 s behind live. The Default Media Receiver buffers whole HLS segments before it plays, so the floor is several segment durations; LL-HLS does not auto-engage there, even when the rendition serves low-latency parts. This is inherent to casting, not a fault — use it for ambient monitoring on TVs, not for time-critical confidence monitoring, and never expect a cast device to join a synchronized wall (cast devices are excluded from sync groups)."
msgstr "Cast playback is Tier D on the sync ladder: seconds-class glass-to-glass latency, typically 6–30 s behind live. The Default Media Receiver buffers whole HLS segments before it plays, so the floor is several segment durations; LL-HLS does not auto-engage there, even when the rendition serves low-latency parts. This is inherent to casting, not a fault — use it for ambient monitoring on TVs, not for time-critical confidence monitoring, and never expect a cast device to join a synchronized wall (cast devices are excluded from sync groups)."

