#: src/pages/docs/CastingHelpPage.tsx:31
msgid "Casting in Multiview is server-initiated: the control plane dials the device's CASTV2 port directly, launches the device's built-in Default Media Receiver, and hands it the URL of an HLS rendition the engine is already serving. It is not browser tab casting — your browser is not involved, nothing is re-encoded, and closing the management UI changes nothing. The device pulls the same rendition every other HLS client gets (encode-once-mux-many), and a cast session is pure control plane: the engine never sees it, so program output can never depend on it."
msgstr "Casting in Multiview is server-initiated: the control plane dials the device's CASTV2 port directly, launches the device's built-in Default Media Receiver, and hands it the URL of an HLS rendition the engine is already serving. It is not browser tab casting — your browser is not involved, nothing is re-encoded, and closing the management UI changes nothing. The device pulls the same rendition every other HLS client gets (encode-once-mux-many), and a cast session is pure control plane: the engine never sees it, so program output can never depend on it."

