#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:187
msgid "Each <0>[[cells]]</0> entry is one tile. It is placed by a grid <1>area</1> or an absolute <2>rect</2>, and binds a source through <3>[cells.source]</3> — usually a reference to a managed source by <4>input_id</4>."
msgstr "Each <0>[[cells]]</0> entry is one tile. It is placed by a grid <1>area</1> or an absolute <2>rect</2>, and binds a source through <3>[cells.source]</3> — usually a reference to a managed source by <4>input_id</4>."

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:331
msgid "Each <0>[[devices]]</0> entry adopts one managed device as desired state: a <1>driver</1> (<2>zowietek</2>, <3>displaynode</3>, or <4>cast</4>), an IPv6-first management <5>address</5> (required for zowietek/cast; optional for an enrolled display node), an optional <6>desired_mode</6> the driver re-converges on every reconnect, an optional <7>alarm_on_offline</7> severity, and write-only credentials via <8>auth.secret_ref</8>. Applying a config adopts and converges idempotently."
msgstr "Each <0>[[devices]]</0> entry adopts one managed device as desired state: a <1>driver</1> (<2>zowietek</2>, <3>displaynode</3>, or <4>cast</4>), an IPv6-first management <5>address</5> (required for zowietek/cast; optional for an enrolled display node), an optional <6>desired_mode</6> the driver re-converges on every reconnect, an optional <7>alarm_on_offline</7> severity, and write-only credentials via <8>auth.secret_ref</8>. Applying a config adopts and converges idempotently."

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:260
msgid "Each <0>[[outputs]]</0> entry is one sink, tagged by <1>kind</1>. The canvas is composited and encoded once, then fanned out to every output. Today, file-based HLS output works; the live network output servers are on the roadmap (see the feature guide)."
msgstr "Each <0>[[outputs]]</0> entry is one sink, tagged by <1>kind</1>. The canvas is composited and encoded once, then fanned out to every output. Today, file-based HLS output works; the live network output servers are on the roadmap (see the feature guide)."

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:228
msgid "Each <0>[[overlays]]</0> entry attaches a layer to the whole <1>canvas</1> or to a single cell. Common kinds are <2>clock</2>, <3>label</3>, and <4>tally_border</4>. Kind-specific parameters (such as a clock <5>format</5>) sit alongside the common fields and round-trip losslessly."
msgstr "Each <0>[[overlays]]</0> entry attaches a layer to the whole <1>canvas</1> or to a single cell. Common kinds are <2>clock</2>, <3>label</3>, and <4>tally_border</4>. Kind-specific parameters (such as a clock <5>format</5>) sit alongside the common fields and round-trip losslessly."

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:143
msgid "Each <0>[[sources]]</0> entry is a managed input with a stable <1>id</1>, an optional <2>display_name</2>, and a <3>kind</3> that selects the transport. The network kinds carry a <4>url</4>; NDI binds by <5>name</5>; file inputs use a <6>path</6>; <7>test</7> is a built-in synthetic pattern with no parameters."
msgstr "Each <0>[[sources]]</0> entry is a managed input with a stable <1>id</1>, an optional <2>display_name</2>, and a <3>kind</3> that selects the transport. The network kinds carry a <4>url</4>; NDI binds by <5>name</5>; file inputs use a <6>path</6>; <7>test</7> is a built-in synthetic pattern with no parameters."

#: src/pages/docs/ConfigPage.tsx:357
msgid "Each <0>[[sync_groups]]</0> entry aligns member devices' presentation: <1>target_skew_ms</1> (1–10000) is the drift-alarm threshold and every member carries a per-device <2>offset_ms</2> trim (0–10000). Cast devices can never be members; the group reports its weakest member's tier."
msgstr "Each <0>[[sync_groups]]</0> entry aligns member devices' presentation: <1>target_skew_ms</1> (1–10000) is the drift-alarm threshold and every member carries a per-device <2>offset_ms</2> trim (0–10000). Cast devices can never be members; the group reports its weakest member's tier."

