msgstr "H.265 (HEVC) compresses roughly 30–50% better than H.264 at the same quality, which matters most at 4K and for 10-bit/HDR content. The trade-offs: encoding costs more compute, patent licensing is more complicated, and playback support — while now broad on hardware — is still patchier in browsers than H.264. Classic RTMP cannot carry it; newer endpoints and MPEG-TS based transports can."

