#: src/pages/docs/concepts/TimingSyncPage.tsx:103
msgid "How Multiview relates: the fixed-cadence output clock free-runs on the host's monotonic clock by default — no timing hardware needed. In a PTP facility the same clock can be <0>disciplined</0> to the grandmaster (its rate gently steered, never stepped), and if the reference disappears the output coasts and then free-runs — it never stops. Inputs remain sampled, never pacing, in every mode; PTP changes how well sources line up with each other, not who controls the output."
msgstr "How Multiview relates: the fixed-cadence output clock free-runs on the host's monotonic clock by default — no timing hardware needed. In a PTP facility the same clock can be <0>disciplined</0> to the grandmaster (its rate gently steered, never stepped), and if the reference disappears the output coasts and then free-runs — it never stops. Inputs remain sampled, never pacing, in every mode; PTP changes how well sources line up with each other, not who controls the output."

