#: src/pages/docs/concepts/TransportsPage.tsx:130
msgid "RTMP is a TCP push protocol that remains the lingua franca for sending a stream <0>to</0> a service — most streaming platforms still ingest it. Classic RTMP carries H.264 video and AAC audio only; newer \"enhanced\" endpoints negotiate H.265 and AV1. As an input it appears when an encoder or app pushes to Multiview; as an output it is how Multiview pushes the composed canvas to a platform."
msgstr "RTMP is a TCP push protocol that remains the lingua franca for sending a stream <0>to</0> a service — most streaming platforms still ingest it. Classic RTMP carries H.264 video and AAC audio only; newer \"enhanced\" endpoints negotiate H.265 and AV1. As an input it appears when an encoder or app pushes to Multiview; as an output it is how Multiview pushes the composed canvas to a platform."

#: src/docs/registry.ts:416
