#: src/pages/docs/concepts/ResiliencePage.tsx:65
msgid "The moment a fresh frame arrives — from any state — the tile snaps straight back to LIVE. The hold, stale, and no-signal windows are automatic: the engine uses built-in, broadcast-tuned values and derives its stream-liveness checks from each source's own frame cadence, so a low-frame-rate source is not misread as stalled. There is nothing for an operator to configure."
msgstr "The moment a fresh frame arrives — from any state — the tile snaps straight back to LIVE. The hold, stale, and no-signal windows are automatic: the engine uses built-in, broadcast-tuned values and derives its stream-liveness checks from each source's own frame cadence, so a low-frame-rate source is not misread as stalled. There is nothing for an operator to configure."

