#: src/pages/docs/concepts/TimingSyncPage.tsx:118
msgid "Wall-clock time is ordinary time-of-day (UTC), kept by the host's system clock and disciplined by NTP or PTP. Multiview uses it for <0>labels only</0>: on-screen clock overlays, log timestamps, and the date-time stamps in HLS playlists. It never paces frames, because a system clock can step backwards or jump when corrected — exactly what an output clock must never do."
msgstr "Wall-clock time is ordinary time-of-day (UTC), kept by the host's system clock and disciplined by NTP or PTP. Multiview uses it for <0>labels only</0>: on-screen clock overlays, log timestamps, and the date-time stamps in HLS playlists. It never paces frames, because a system clock can step backwards or jump when corrected — exactly what an output clock must never do."

